{
  "answer": "**The specified ghazal, \"Yeh na thi hamari qismat ke visaal-e-yaar hota\" (Diwan-E-Ghalib, ch. 204), does not contain any couplet referring to a \"world's preacher\" (or equivalents like zahid/mullah/priest) or their \"tongue cleaved in two\" (or concepts like split/forked/cleft tongue).**[^1][^2]\n\nI searched the full English translation, transliteration, and original Urdu text of the chapter, as well as the broader corpus for related phrases (e.g., \"preacher\", \"tongue\", \"cleaved\", \"world preacher\", \"zahid\", \"zuban\"). No matches appear. The ghazal laments unfulfilled love, false promises, inevitable sorrow, and mystical unity, but nothing about preachers or cleaved tongues.[^3][^4][^5]\n\nIf this is a misremembered couplet from another Ghalib ghazal (e.g., involving zahid/piety critiques elsewhere in the Diwan), or from a different translation/edition not in this corpus, it's not present here.\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 204 (\"Yeh na thi hamari qismat...\"), [translation](https://falsafa.corpus/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/translation/#p-e43078).\n[^2]: Ibid., [transliteration](https://falsafa.corpus/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/transliteration/#p-007848).\n[^3]: Ibid., [original](https://falsafa.corpus/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/204-yeh-na-thi-hamari-qismat-ke-visaal-e-yaar-hota/original/#p-0ed9be).\n[^4]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib* work wiki card, [work-level](https://falsafa.corpus/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/wiki/_work.card.md).\n[^5]: Corpus search: \"preacher tongue\", \"world preacher\", etc. (0 results in this work).",
